\h1{The \tt{echo-config} program}

\h2{Interface}
<pre>
  echo-config \it{user} \it{loguser} \it{dir} \it{port}
</pre>
where \ti{user} and \ti{loguser} are system account names,
\ti{dir} is an absolute path name, and \ti{port} is a TCP port.
The port may be specified as a name from \tt{/etc/services} or a
numeric value.

\tt{echo-config} creates the directory \ti{dir} as an
\a{http://cr.yp.to/daemontools/svscan.html}{svscan}-format service
directory, configured to run \tt{echo-httpd} on the TCP port
\ti{port}, running \tt{echo-httpd} as \ti{user} and creating log
files as \ti{loguser}.


